<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2013-05-07</DATELINE><TITLE>Reinvigorating the Role of Science in Democracy</TITLE><BODY>Private and political interests routinely conspire to sideline and misrepresent science and evidence in the public policy process. The Center for Science and Democracy, a new initiative at the Union of Concerned Scientists, endeavors to change this dynamic to strengthen the role of science in decision making.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>